EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to water; creating the Fund for Hydrological
Studies to make grants of money for hydrological studies
in certain counties; revising provisions governing the
payment of the cost of a hydrological study required by
the State Engineer in certain counties; making an
appropriation to the Fund to be used for such grants of
money; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law: (1) authorizes the State Engineer to require a hydrological,
2 environmental or any other study be conducted before the State Engineer approves
3 or rejects an application to apply water to beneficial use if such a study has not
4 been conducted by the applicant, a governmental agency or other person or the
5 study is not available; and (2) requires the applicant to bear the full cost of the
6 study. (NRS 533.368, 533.370) Any money collected from the applicant to perform
7 the study is required under existing law to be deposited in the Account for Studies
8 Concerning Water and used to defray the costs of conducting these studies and
9 certain inventories. (NRS 533.369)
10 Section 1 of this bill creates a Fund for Hydrological Studies and, with certain
11 exceptions, requires, for a hydrological study which is required by the State
12 Engineer to be conducted in a county whose population is less than 100,000
13 (currently all counties other than Clark and Washoe Counties): (1) an applicant to
14 pay a deposit to defray 50 percent of the cost of such a study; and (2) the State
15 Engineer to make a grant of money from the Fund equal to the amount deposited by
16 the applicant to defray the remaining 50 percent of the cost of such a study. Section
17 1 further requires, if there is insufficient money in the Fund to make such a grant of
18 money, the State Engineer to make a grant of money from the Account for Studies
19 Concerning Water to cover the remaining costs. If the Account also has insufficient
20 money to cover the remaining amount, section 1 authorizes the applicant to: (1) pay
21 a cash deposit to the State Engineer in an amount sufficient to defray the remaining
