8 except as otherwise provided in subsection 4, the applicant must
9 pay a cash deposit to the State Engineer which is sufficient to
10 defray 50 percent of the cost of the study.
11 3. Upon the applicant paying a cash deposit pursuant to
12 subsection 2, the State Engineer shall, except as otherwise
13 provided in this section, make a grant of money from the Fund
14 equal to the amount deposited by the applicant to pay the
15 remaining cost of the study. If there is insufficient money
16 available in:
17 (a) The Fund, the State Engineer shall make a grant of money
18 from the Account for Studies Concerning Water established by
19 NRS 533.369 to defray any remaining cost of the study.
20 (b) The Account for Studies Concerning Water, the applicant
21 may:
22 (1) Pay the remaining cost of the study; or
23 (2) Withdraw his or her application and receive a refund of
24 any money deposited pursuant to subsection 2.
25 4. The State Engineer or a person designated by the State
26 Engineer shall not conduct a hydrological study required pursuant
27 to subsection 1 of NRS 533.368 until the full cost of the study is
28 paid in accordance with the requirements of this section.
